{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> πίτυς</b> [ῐ], υος, ἡ, <br /> <i>Epic dialect</i> <i>dative</i> <i>plural</i> πίτυσσιν, <b>pine</b>, especially <b>Pinus Laricio, Corsican pine</b>, π. βλωθρή, τήν τ᾽ οὔρεσι τέκτονες ἄνδρες ἐξέταμον [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 13.390; μακρῇσίν τε πίτυσσιν ἰδὲ δρυσίν 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 9.186 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; also, <b>Aleppo pine, P. halepensis</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-3rd c.BC: Theophrastus Philosophus “Historia Plantarum” 3.9.5, 2nd c.BC: Nicander Epicus “Alexipharmaca” 301, 2nd c.AD: Pausanias Periegeta 2.1.3, “Geoponica” 2.8.2 (called π. ἀγρία 4th-3rd c.BC: Theophrastus Philosophus “Historia Plantarum” 1.9.3, 3.3.1, 2nd c.AD: Pausanias Periegeta 5.6.4)\">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]; <b>stone pine, P. pinea</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 3rd c.BC: Theocritus Poeta Bucolicus 5.49, 1st c.AD: Dioscorides (Dioscurides) Medicus 1.69, 72 (π. ἥμερος 2nd c.AD: Pausanias Periegeta 6.9.1)\">Refs 3rd c.BC+</a>]; <b>small-seeded pine, P. brutia</b>, π. φθειροποιός [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-3rd c.BC: Theophrastus Philosophus “Historia Plantarum” 2.2.6, compare 1st c.AD: Plinius Rerum Naturalium Scriptor “Historia Naturalis” 16.49 \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]; the <b>Isthmian pine</b> was one species, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 3rd c.BC(?): Callixinus Historicus 2, 1st-2nd c.AD: Plutarchus Biographus et Philosophus 2.675e: proverbial, πίτυος τρόπον ἐκτρίβειν\">Refs 3rd c.BC+</a>] like <b>a pine</b>, i.e. <b>utterly</b>, because the pine when cut down never grows again, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 6.37 (but this is attributed to the πεύκη, and not to the πίτυς, by 4th-3rd c.BC: Theophrastus Philosophus “Historia Plantarum” 3.9.5). \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]","strongNumber":"G8797","accentedUnicode":"πίτυς","shortDef":"pine tree","mediumDef":"pine tree","stepGloss":"pine tree","stepTransliteration":"pitus","count":0,"_step_Type":"word"}]}